Nairobi Governor Mike Sonko has organised a 2-day free medical camp in honour of his late father Gideon Kivanguli. The camp will be hosted at Kathiani primary school, which is opposite Sonko's family farm at Mua hills in Machakos county, on Thursday and Friday. Sonko's father died in September 2015, this being the third anniversary of his death. Various medical conditions will be handled at the camp and complex ones referred to hospitals. Wiper Party leader Kalonzo Musyoka is expected to officially open the camp as a chief guest. Click here for the latest political news         